title: Zone 5 Training on Stairmaster
content: Peter's approach to zone 5 training involves using a stairmaster once per week. He follows a 4-minute pattern of 3 minutes of zone 2 and 1 minute at his VO2 max, which he repeats for 20-30 minutes. He usually does this on the tail end of a zone two workout.

title: Zone 5 Training on Bike
content: Peter also does zone 5 training on his bike, which involves four minutes at 125% of FTP followed by four minutes of recovery. He follows a one to one work/rest at a lower intensity than the 3 to 1 one rest to work that described on the stairmaster.

title: Peter's View on Zone 5 Training
content: Peter believes that most people spend too much time in zone 5 and not enough time in zone 2.
